    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I did not understand till a very short time since, that I was oblig’d to You for
                    two Prints which you was kind enough to leave at Bretherton’s<note type="editorial">This may refer to <persName ref="pe0320">James
                            Bretherton</persName>, engraver and printseller at <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0758">134 New Bond Street</placeName> from 1771 to 1799.
                        Exeter Working Papers in Book History @bookhistory.blogspot.co.uk
                        [ABB]</note> for me. I desire to give you my best thanks for them, and to
                    assure you that I think myself very much honor’d in having a place in your
                    remembrance. I have built a House in <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0759">Stratton
                        Street Picadilly</placeName>,<note type="editorial">
                        <persName ref="pe0313">Richard Bull</persName>'s house in town was
                            <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0759">no. 10 Stratton Street</placeName>.
                        Evans, ‘Richard Bull and Thomas Pennant’, 271. The earliest letter from
                            <persName ref="pe0232">Pennant</persName> addressed to
                            <persName ref="pe0313">Bull</persName> there is NLW 5500C, no.
                        4, [no. IN THIS EDITION] 20 April 1780.</note> and if business or amusement
                    should call you to <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0699">London</placeName> next
                    winter, I should have a real pleasure in seeing you there, because you always
                    amuse and inform me, &amp; I have besides some few things, which I wish to ask
                    your opinion of.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Dear Sir Yours very much</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0313">Rich<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>:
                        Bull</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="pldb.xml#pl0757">Watcombe Place
                            Southampton</placeName> 28 June 1778</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
